useState-Hook
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The useState hook is used to manage the state of a functional component in React.

But what exactly is state?

State is data that belongs to a component and can change over time. It represents information that affects what is displayed on the screen. Examples of state include:

a counter value
text entered into an input field
whether a modal is open or closed
a list of items
user information fetched from an API

In React, functional components are re-executed whenever they re-render. Normally, regular variables do not persist between renders, meaning their values are reset each time the component function runs again.

The useState hook solves this problem by allowing React to:

preserve data between renders
track changes to that data
automatically re-render the component when the state changes
